1.4 Ideal Settling Tank & Overflow Rate
An ideal settling tank has four zones: Inlet zone (uniform flow distribution), Settling zone (quiescent settling),
Sludge zone (collected sediment), and Outlet zone (clarified effluent withdrawal).
Surface Overflow Rate (SOR) – Key Design Parameter
SOR = Q / A_s = v_s (critical settling velocity)
Where: Q = flow rate (m³/day); A_s = surface area of tank (m²)
Any particle with v_s ³ SOR will be COMPLETELY removed (100% removal)
Particles with v_s < SOR are partially removed proportionally: removal % = v_s/SOR × 100
