4. Filtration
Filtration is the process of passing water through a porous medium to remove suspended solids, colloidal
particles, and microorganisms. It follows sedimentation in water treatment and is a critical barrier to pathogens.
Filtration removes particles too small to settle even after coagulation–flocculation.
